
[1]despotism

   DESPOTISM, n.

   1. Absolute power; authority unlimited and uncontrolled by men,
   constitution or laws, and depending alone on the will of the prince; as
   the despotism of a Turkish sultan.

   2. An arbitrary government, as that of Turkey and Persia.
